  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results are reported using aggregate RMSE and R^2 across all five flow-speed operating points, which appear rigorous but do not directly address the COU question of identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions — a task requiring rank-order fidelity and peak-error characterisation rather than mean-fit statistics.",
